Module1:

What is Agentic AI
An Agentic AI workflow is a Process  where LLM Based App Execute Many Steps to complete the task
Example : write a essay on dinasaurs 
Direct Flow -> LLM -> response
Agentic Flow 	-> LLM go research
		-> LLM draft intial essay (draft)
		-> LLM judge/Refractor that, and suggest changes (more tha one time) 
		-> LLM Send to human Review

Degree of Autonomy
Less Autonomous : Flow is Defined, All Step Predifined, All tool use use hard coded, Autonomy is in text generation.
semi autonomous: Agent can make some decision and choose tools, tools are usually Predifined
More Autonomous: At each Step LLM decide to take which step, Agent Makes Decision, can create new tool on the fly.

Benifits of Agents:
1) Earlier Generation Model Surpass new Generation Model in Benchmarks Using Agents [Performance Improvement]
2) Steps in Work flow can be parallelized, can helps to speed up the tasks [Faster (Parallization)]
3) Modular: Flexible Component add/swap change configuration of components [Flexible]

